{"lemma":"فَقِيهٌ","slug":"فَقِيهٌ","root":"ف.ق.ه","root_slug":"ف-ق-ه","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ق-ه","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34365"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%87%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"jurist and theologian, expert in Islamic jurisprudence, faqih"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"reciter of the Qur'an"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"teacher of the Qur'an in a quranic school"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/fa.qiːh/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34365","headword_ar":"فَقِيهٌ","root":"fqh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"Any one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing knowledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fafiyhu AlEarabi","text_ar":"فَفِيهُ العَرَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAlim","text_ar":"عَالِم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"man of knowledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Arabs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and was an appellation given to El-Hárith Ibn-Keledeh ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlH`rivu","text_ar":"الحٰرِثُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bonu kaladapa","text_ar":"بْنُ كَلَدَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), who was also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tabiybu AlEarabi","text_ar":"طَبِيبُ العَرَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as is said in the S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Azm","text_ar":"ازم"},{"kind":"text","text":"], because this appellation is syn. with the former; but IKh and El- Hareeree do not mean by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fqyhA lErb","text_ar":"فقيها لعرب"},{"kind":"text","text":"any particular person. (Mz, close of the 39th"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwE","text_ar":"نوع"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  [Particularly and predominantly,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqiyhN","text_ar":"فَقِيهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing knowledge of the law;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lawyer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faquhN","text_ar":"فَقُهٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K;) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqiyhapN","text_ar":"فَقِيهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faquhapN","text_ar":"فَقُهَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl. [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqiyhN","text_ar":"فَقِيهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuqahaA='u","text_ar":"فُقَهَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fafiyhapN","text_ar":"فَفِيهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqaAy^ihu","text_ar":"فَقَايِهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuqahaA='u","text_ar":"فُقَهَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2430},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) the last of these pls. mentioned by Lh, and anomalous, as applied to women: ISd says, “ in my opinion, he, of the Arabs, who says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuqahaA='","text_ar":"فُقَهَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in speaking of women] takes no account of the fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": it is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuqaraA='u","text_ar":"فُقَرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to women. ” (TA.) [In Egypt, the appellation"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiqiY","text_ar":"فِقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", a vulgar corruption of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqiyh","text_ar":"فَقِيه"},{"kind":"text","text":", is now applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A schoolmaster;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person who recites the Kur-án &c. for hire."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHolN faqiyhN","text_ar":"فَحْلٌ فَقِيهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stallion"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expert in covering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that knows well the she-camels that are lusting, and the pregnant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}